The candidate response directly addresses the core diagnostics before making changes and aligns tightly with the rubric’s method: it asks for the loss curve and gradient norms, prescribes a tiny-batch overfit test, and recommends an LR range test rather than guessing. It explicitly rejects jumping to a bigger model and sequences diagnostics before any hyperparameter changes. Evidence is plentiful and explicit for each criterion.

