      "reasoning": "It prescribes overfitting a tiny batch of 8 examples to near-zero loss before other actions.",
      "score": 1
    },
    {
      "criterion": "suggests_lr_sweep_or_range_test",
      "evidence": "\"then do an LR-range test (1e-7 → 1e-3, short ramp) — 1e-5 is folklore and may be 10× off for your specific setup... sweep, do not copy.\"",
      "reasoning": "It clearly recommends an LR range test with explicit bounds and rationale.",
      "score": 1
    },
    {
      "criterion": "avoids_recommending_bigger_model_immediately",
      "evidence": "\"I need to rule out a broken loop before anyone touches the model size.\" and \"Do not change model size.\" and \"High that 'try a bigger model' is the wrong next step.\"",
      "reasoning": "It explicitly declines the bigger model suggestion and explains why.",
      "score": 1
    },
    {
      "criterion": "avoids_skipping_diagnostic_for_action",
      "evidence": "\"Evidence I need from you before recommending anything:\" followed by diagnostic steps, and in Fix: sequencing diagnostics (overfit test, label alignment, grad norms) before LR sweep.",
      "reasoning": "It demands diagnostics first and does not jump straight to tuning without evidence.",
      "score": 1
    }
  ],
